Joyous Mackdaddy, 23rd Human Enchanter of Sullon Zek [Test], Anarchy (Player Wiped)<br><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukuulq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kuulq</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/8/01 1:03:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rallos </span><hr size=1> Kanbic, can you explain why ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=skitch>Skitch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/8/01 1:23:15 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rallos </span><hr size=1> I just picked a random thread to ask this, but what are the rulesets for the PK servers now? I went back 7 pages of threads and only saw stuff on Sullon, gave up and decided to just ask.<br>
<br>
My friend and I created dwarves on Rallos when Veeshan was down the other night - only level 4, so no PK yet, but curious as to where the rules might differ.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
Skitch <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaximilean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maximilean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/8/01 8:53:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Rules</span><hr size=1> Sullon:<br>
<br>
No level limits, no rules regarding training, bind rushing, bind camping, etc.  Kills within a 5 level range invoke coin loot and xp-loss.  SZ also has a system of points and insignia that is a little complex, it's on EQ's page fairly prominently.<br>
<br>
Vallon/Tallon:<br>
<br>
Team server, teams being Good Elves, Humans, Shorties, Evils.  +-8 level range for pvp, rules still in effect.  Supposedly Vallon will be hard-coded to prevent crossteaming in the future; it is suspected Elves and Pecks may be joined as a team, much to everyone's horror.<br>
<br>
Rallos:<br>
<br>
PVP Range is +-4, item loot is in effect.  No teams, etc.<br>
<br>
Vallon was fun, but if I were you I'd definately start on SZ at this point.  It's where the energy is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/9/01 12:01:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rules</span><hr size=1> I would NOT start a melee on sz, as a pvp newbie youll just get spanked time and time again. since all a  caster has to do is run (even unsowed) to get away from you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/box.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/9/01 3:56:19 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/Kambic/TRINITY.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rules</span><hr size=1> What she ^ said. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uannid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anni D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/9/01 9:41:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rules</span><hr size=1> Another very important push against melee that is unique to Sullon is that you can dispel the enemy teams. Damage shield=dead melee and the caster just needs to sit there and watch you kill yourself. Now that is what I call balance.<br>
<br>
-Anni<br>
<br>
*edit:hehe. I just noticed I misspelled sullon when I made my sig those weeks ago. Maybe Ill go fix it now haha. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uannid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anni D</A> at: 8/10/01 10:12:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/10/01 8:24:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rallos </span><hr size=1> Its not just game mechanics or a rule set. Let me explain what makes good pvp and why Rallos doesn't have it.<br>
<br>
1. Control over your own fate. Human being as a rule want to feel like the choices they make effect their fates for good or ill.  We like to think that if we play skillfully we will get ahead.  Even if we lose we would like to have had an interesting experience and try to figure out what to do next time.<br>
<br>
2. Fair resolution of combat.  Pvp combat exists for the sake of fun conflect, resolution of issues by force, and deciding who is stronger in pvp. There are choices for both the weaker and the stronger party and (a) it works best when the loser doesn't resort to cheap methods like training the winners because he can't beat them and  it works well if (b) the winner doesn't abuse the loser beyond beating him. No need to harass people for your own amusement.<br>
<br>
3.  A sense of community.  A guild or group should build a rep and the community should provide a natural mechanism to limit people who abuse 1 or 2 by supporting other parties against those who are losers and exist only to choose their victims then harass and  train them then train them again as they are rezed so they can crack jokes in /gu.<br>
<br>
Rallos doesn't have any of those things. You don't have 1 because no matter how good you are its likely cheap dorks will end up some of your stuff because 2a doesn't happen people fight as cheap as they wish for whatever reason as long as they win and this is so much the norm that nobody cares.  Nor do you have 3 because there are so many pricks and bullies rather than pvpers that nobody helps anyone but their immediate allies who they are SURE will help em back.<br>
<br>
In my experience the large portion of 50+ don't want to get involved, can't afford to get involved, or are out starting bs conflicts in order to screw people over themselves.<br>
<br>
I think I miss the 30s...<br>
<br>
